{# User prompt body for stock report generation.
   Variables: analysis (StockAnalysis), news (NewsBundle).
   The system message (role + JSON schema) lives in stock_report_system.j2. #}
Symbol: {{ analysis.symbol }}
Analysis timestamp: {{ analysis.timestamp.isoformat() }}
Last close: Rs. {{ "%.2f"|format(analysis.features.last_close) }}

## Quantitative recommendation: {{ analysis.recommendation }}
Rationale (deterministic): {{ analysis.recommendation_rationale }}

## Composite score: {{ "%.3f"|format(analysis.score) }} / 1.000

### Sub-scores (each in [0, 1])
- Moving averages: {{ "%.3f"|format(analysis.sub_scores.moving_average) }}
- Momentum: {{ "%.3f"|format(analysis.sub_scores.momentum) }}
- Volume: {{ "%.3f"|format(analysis.sub_scores.volume) }}
- Volatility: {{ "%.3f"|format(analysis.sub_scores.volatility) }}
- Fundamental: {{ "%.3f"|format(analysis.sub_scores.fundamental) }}
- Support / resistance: {{ "%.3f"|format(analysis.sub_scores.support_resistance) }}
- Trend-following (MACD): {{ "%.3f"|format(analysis.sub_scores.trend_following) }}
- Mean-reversion (Bollinger): {{ "%.3f"|format(analysis.sub_scores.mean_reversion) }}

### Moving averages
- SMA20 / SMA50 / SMA200: {{ "%.2f"|format(analysis.moving_averages.sma_20) }} / {{ "%.2f"|format(analysis.moving_averages.sma_50) }} / {{ "%.2f"|format(analysis.moving_averages.sma_200) }}
- EMA12 / EMA26: {{ "%.2f"|format(analysis.moving_averages.ema_12) }} / {{ "%.2f"|format(analysis.moving_averages.ema_26) }}
- Alignment: {{ analysis.moving_averages.alignment }}
- SMA50 slope: {{ analysis.moving_averages.sma50_slope }}; SMA200 slope: {{ analysis.moving_averages.sma200_slope }}
- Price vs SMA20 / SMA50 / SMA200: {{ "%+.2f"|format(analysis.moving_averages.price_to_sma20_pct) }}% / {{ "%+.2f"|format(analysis.moving_averages.price_to_sma50_pct) }}% / {{ "%+.2f"|format(analysis.moving_averages.price_to_sma200_pct) }}%
{%- if analysis.moving_averages.crossover %}
- Recent crossover: {{ analysis.moving_averages.crossover }} ({{ analysis.moving_averages.crossover_days_ago }} day(s) ago)
{%- else %}
- Recent crossover: none
{%- endif %}

### Momentum
- RSI(14): {{ "%.1f"|format(analysis.features.momentum.rsi_14) }}
- Returns: 5d {{ "%+.2f"|format(analysis.features.momentum.return_5d * 100) }}%, 10d {{ "%+.2f"|format(analysis.features.momentum.return_10d * 100) }}%, 20d {{ "%+.2f"|format(analysis.features.momentum.return_20d * 100) }}%

### Volume
- Current: {{ analysis.features.volume.current_volume }}, 20d avg: {{ "%.0f"|format(analysis.features.volume.avg_volume_20d) }}
- Ratio (current / 20d avg): {{ "%.2f"|format(analysis.features.volume.volume_ratio) }}x
- OBV: {{ "%.0f"|format(analysis.features.volume.obv) }}

### Volatility
- ATR(14): {{ "%.2f"|format(analysis.features.volatility.atr_14) }}
- Std dev (20d): {{ "%.2f"|format(analysis.features.volatility.std_dev_20) }}

### Support / resistance
- 52w high: {{ "%.2f"|format(analysis.features.support_resistance.high_52w) }} ({{ "%+.2f"|format(analysis.features.support_resistance.distance_to_52w_high_pct) }}%)
- 52w low: {{ "%.2f"|format(analysis.features.support_resistance.low_52w) }} ({{ "%+.2f"|format(analysis.features.support_resistance.distance_to_52w_low_pct) }}%)
- Near 52w high: {{ analysis.features.support_resistance.near_52w_high }}; near 52w low: {{ analysis.features.support_resistance.near_52w_low }}

### MACD (12/26/9)
{%- if analysis.features.macd %}
- MACD line / signal / histogram: {{ "%.3f"|format(analysis.features.macd.macd_line) }} / {{ "%.3f"|format(analysis.features.macd.signal_line) }} / {{ "%+.3f"|format(analysis.features.macd.histogram) }}
- Histogram sign: {{ "positive (bullish momentum)" if analysis.features.macd.histogram > 0 else ("negative (bearish momentum)" if analysis.features.macd.histogram < 0 else "flat") }}
{%- if analysis.features.macd.crossover %}
- Recent signal-line crossover: {{ analysis.features.macd.crossover }} ({{ analysis.features.macd.crossover_days_ago }} day(s) ago)
{%- else %}
- Recent signal-line crossover: none
{%- endif %}
{%- else %}
- Insufficient history — MACD not computed.
{%- endif %}

### Bollinger Bands (20, 2σ)
{%- if analysis.features.bollinger %}
- Upper / middle / lower: {{ "%.2f"|format(analysis.features.bollinger.upper) }} / {{ "%.2f"|format(analysis.features.bollinger.middle) }} / {{ "%.2f"|format(analysis.features.bollinger.lower) }}
- %B (price position inside bands, 0 = lower, 1 = upper): {{ "%.2f"|format(analysis.features.bollinger.percent_b) }}
- Bandwidth: {{ "%.2f"|format(analysis.features.bollinger.bandwidth * 100) }}% ({{ "squeeze" if analysis.features.bollinger.squeeze else "normal" }})
{%- else %}
- Insufficient history — Bollinger Bands not computed.
{%- endif %}

### Fundamentals
- PE: {{ analysis.features.fundamentals.pe if analysis.features.fundamentals.pe is not none else "N/A" }}
{%- if analysis.features.fundamentals.pe_vs_sector_median is not none %}
- PE vs sector median: {{ "%+.2f"|format(analysis.features.fundamentals.pe_vs_sector_median) }}
{%- endif %}
- Market cap tier: {{ analysis.features.fundamentals.market_cap_tier if analysis.features.fundamentals.market_cap_tier else "N/A" }}
{%- if analysis.features.fundamentals.roe is not none %}
- ROE: {{ "%.2f"|format(analysis.features.fundamentals.roe * 100) }}%
{%- endif %}
{%- if analysis.features.fundamentals.roe_sector_rank is not none %}
- ROE sector percentile: {{ "%.2f"|format(analysis.features.fundamentals.roe_sector_rank) }}
{%- endif %}

### Signals
{% for name, value in analysis.signals.items() -%}
- {{ name }}: {{ value }}
{% endfor %}
### News — {{ news.article_count }} article(s) over last {{ news.time_window_hours }}h
Aggregate sentiment: {{ "%+.3f"|format(news.aggregate_sentiment) }}
{% if news.articles %}
Recent headlines (sentiment label / score — URL):
{% for article in news.articles[:10] -%}
- [{{ article.sentiment.label }} / {{ "%+.2f"|format(article.sentiment.score) }}] {{ article.title }} — {{ article.source }} — {{ article.url }}
{% endfor %}
{%- else -%}
No recent news available.
{%- endif %}

Produce the structured report now. Base every statement on the facts above.
Do not invent numbers or URLs. Do not modify the quantitative score.

In addition to the narrative fields, provide your *own* BUY/HOLD/SELL call
(field: `recommendation`) formed by weighing the news, momentum, and context
above. This can agree or disagree with the deterministic `{{ analysis.recommendation }}`
call — when you disagree, state why in `recommendation_rationale` (1-2 sentences).
Leave the `sources` array empty — the service will fill it from the article list.
